Text:
The Cult of Diablos' Rounds. Uncover their secrets
and weaken their power...

The Shadow Garden will set up a base in the
Velgalta Empire and begin an investigation
into the Rounds!
The Velgalta Empire...!
Woohoo! Are we gonna fight?!

Yes, we're going to fight. And it's not just any
fight. We're up against a formidable adversary
unlike any we've faced before.
Strong and big prey! Can't wait to get started!
Beta, Gamma, give Epsilon the details.

The main objectives of this plan are to investigate
and neutralize Sergey Gorman, a Child of the Cult
of Diablos, and to gather intel on the Cult's Rounds.

The plan will progress by accomplishing two
preliminary milestones to ensure we successfully
achieve these objectives.
The first is to secure a foothold in the City States.

The City States form a vital region connecting Midgar
and Velgalta, making them an essential midpoint for
carrying out operations within the Velgalta Empire.

And the second is to establish a Mitsugoshi store
in Velgalta.

The aim is not only to secure a key base for the
Shadow Garden within the Velgalta Empire through
this branch but also to generate operational funds
for the organization and create new sources of intel.
Sounds complicated...and boring...

Typical Beta and Gamma with their practical and
business-minded approach.

Our expansion into the Velgalta Empire has already
been finalized, but Epsilon, do you have any thoughts
on this?
Let's see...

Have we already decided on a location for the
foothold in the City States?
No, not yet.

Since it's an archipelago, our options may be
limited... We'll need to investigate, similar to
what we two did last time.

...If we're uncertain about a location, how about
utilizing No. 111's connections?
No. 111's connections?
Epsilonâ€”

I received a report from Lambda indicating that
No. 111 has yet to reach a level where she can be
deployed into combat.

I'm aware of that as well. Nevertheless, I believe we
should utilize whatever resources we have.
What do you mean specifically?

...The Herzog Family has a secret villa in the
college town of Laugus.
A secret villa?!

Laugus is a hub for cutting-edge research in magic
and artifacts.

And in Laugus, there is a culture among aristocrats
who recognize the value of research. They own villas
that appear outwardly for vacation purposes but are
covertly used as bases for gathering information.

What's important is that these villa estates serve as
arenas for secret skirmishes over cutting-edge
research.

That's why there's an unwritten rule among the
aristocracy not to publicly acknowledge conflicts
occurring within the college town.
So complicated! And boring!

Ugh... Simply put, I believe it would be convenient
for us, the Shadow Garden, to set up a base in Laugus
with No. 111 as our guide!

...So you're suggesting that even if there were to be
skirmishes with the Cult of Diablos or the Templars
of the Holy State, the likelihood of them becoming
publicly known is low.

I understand the rationale, but aren't you also
showing favoritism toward No. 111?

Hardly! My decision isn't driven by personal
emotions! I genuinely believe it's the best
course of action for the Shadow Garden!

Though it appears Beta and Gamma have beaten me to
the punch in proposing a plan...

...You're not even very good at telling half-truths,
Epsilon. It's pretty obvious you're invested in
No. 111.
However, as a proposal, it does seem appealing.

Establishing a smaller Garden base in Laugus could
yield greater returns than our original plan,
offering ongoing advantages!
Are you also favoring No. 111, Gamma?

No, not at all! It's not about favoritism! My opinion
is purely based on what would benefit the Garden!

So, we have Epsilon and Gamma in favor, while Beta
and I are undecided. Delta, what are your thoughts on
including No. 111 in the plan?

I'm fine with anything so long as I can fight no
holds barred! Whether No. 111 is there or not
doesn't matter to me!
Lady Alpha...!

Heheh... It's settled then. We'll make use of the
Herzog Family's secret villa.
Thank you!

However, to be cautious, I'll lay out three
conditions.

Firstly, you'll lead this plan and secure the
foothold in Laugus while overseeing No. 111's
progress.

Secondly, until the base in Laugus is securely
established, Lambda will accompany you as a
strategic advisor, providing insights into local
information.

And, thirdly...no matter how much you favor No. 111,
it will ultimately all depend on her own efforts.
Understood!
Then I'll go and call Lambda and No. 111!

We've decided to officially admit a former Cult
leader into the Garden and have her join a mission.
Right...

I remained cautious until the very end, but it seems
Gamma has been assessing her from the start.

(Sounds like she managed to soft land Gamma's recent
move.)

(As for the unexpected encounter in that remote
corner, it seems she decided to power through it.)

(Well, sometimes it's wiser to go with the flow and
push forward rather than desperately trying to
piece everything together perfectly.)

(It's like those battle manga I used to read in my
past life, where characters you thought were dead
suddenly come back to life...)

(Or even cases where, in lengthy serializations, an
author forgets a character was meant to be dead,
and they unexpectedly reappear, causing quite a stir.)

(In essence...even experts in the field sometimes
prioritize momentum over consistency.)

Epsilon will guide her effectively. She's a hard
worker and has a knack for understanding others'
intentions.

There shouldn't be an issue as long as we're not
currently engaged in direct conflict with her.
Whether she'll betray us later is another matter.

Above all, as the Shadow Garden, we must avoid the
pitfalls that arise from the complexities of emotionsâ€”
namely, falling into a cycle of hatred...

Yes, you're absolutely right. That's why Epsilon is
the most fitting choice...

And we must always strive to help those afflicted by
possession, no matter the circumstances. It's one of
the core principles that define the Garden's
existence!
But, Alpha...tread carefully.
Cid?

(That's right! There's something that's gotta be
pointed out in situations like this!)

Most of those we persuade to join us, whether neutral
party or enemy leader...
Yes, go on...

Once they become our allies and undergo a significant
circumstantial and emotional change, their abilities
somehow weaken.
*gasp*

You immediately perceived what only Epsilon, Lambda,
and I discovered in Alexandria... You never cease to
amaze me, Cid.
Y-Yeah...

(Al-Alpha is incredible... She nailed that comeback.
Her ad-libbing skills continue to improve!)

Even factoring in No. 111's skill with the slime
sword, her performance is noticeably below her
previous combat records!

I'll have Epsilon keep a close eye on her for now.
Thank you for your advice, Cid.
Heh... Constant vigilance!

(Well, it's true that redemption arcs can often lead
to a decline in raw abilities due to undergoing
environmental and emotional changes.)

(And...that's precisely why I aspire to be a
shadowbroker who isn't swayed by such
situational and mental pitfalls!)
